Name: John Smith
Age: 62
Gender: Male
Occupation: Retired
Ethnicity: Caucasian
Past Medical History: Hypertension, hyperlipidemia, type 2 diabetes, prostate cancer (in remission for 5 years)
Key Complaints: Fatigue, bone pain (especially in the ribs and back), recurrent infections, weight loss.

Name: Sarah Johnson
Age: 62
Gender: Female
Occupation: Retired teacher
Ethnicity: Caucasian
Past Medical History: Hypertension, hyperlipidemia, osteoporosis, and recent history of recurrent infections.

Key Complaints: Sarah presents to her primary care physician with complaints of fatigue, weakness, and bone pain. She reports difficulty walking due to pain in her lower back and legs. She has also noticed recent weight loss and decreased appetite. Upon further evaluation, lab work reveals anemia and elevated levels of protein in her urine. A subsequent bone marrow biopsy confirms a diagnosis of multiple myeloma.
